agent.housing experience: Initially, I lived in a shared rental apartment in the Inner Sunset with roommates to manage high rental costs. After two years, I moved to a studio in the Outer Sunset to gain more privacy, but increasing rent and job instability during the pandemic forced me to relocate again. I then moved in temporarily with family in the Excelsior District before securing a more affordable one-bedroom unit through a housing assistance program.
